@exscape Exactly this. There isn't much potential to improve speed for more than 15% when 1) there is still no real option for a more advanced process node, and 2) TSMC 4 nm wafers have become 15% MORE EXPENSIVE since 2021.
So in order to maintain or slightly reduce MSRP,  Nvidia has opted for chips of the same size but with some optimisation. Like the 4070Ti Super had 8448 cores on 379 mm, while the 5070Ti has 8960 cores on 378 mm.

AMD and Intel are in the same boat. Both the upcoming 9700XT and the B580 are also based on TSMC 4nm.

